The transaction is thus permanently linked to the chain of all other transactions, and any modification would change the fingerprint.
If a user wants to pay for the same money very quickly (less than 10 minutes) twice for the scam, only one of the two transactions would be validated by the network and the other would be unlinked because both have different fingerprints.
The computer that solves the problem gets 50 bitcoins.
