The initiative to introduce the tests was supported by the Members of the State Duma and the Federal Migration Agency.
But before the law came into force, civil rights activists repeatedly asked the press: What is the point of all this?
What changes will the requirement to have language skills bring for both Russians and guest workers?
The main aim, according to a spokesman for the Migration Agency, is to reduce the number of forced labourers.
