I've experienced that the tutors not only tolerated the ridicule of Tory students, but even took part with pleasure.
Political issues such as the miners' strike, privatization and the government's rejection of sanctions against South Africa's apartheid regime found their way into the wood-paved rooms of the tutorial.
At my first such event, I was supposed to translate 18th-century French texts into English, but I was not prepared for what was to come.
"Miss Wyatt", said tutor Harry Pitt (who has since died), "please translate the first paragraph".
I stumbled on it.
Pitt was a little man with a face like a pie pie pie, and pretty nasty.
