Privacy
According to the dictionary, this is the private property or "the area of private life where one is entitled to protection from any kind of interference".
What's private for someone under 16?
How does this definition apply to his everyday life and social networks?
Does he understand the dangers he faces when he publishes online situations he would not share in real life?
El Periódico interviewed five teenagers aged 10 to 15 who are often online.
