The teachers never commit to anything, and in return, we always sign everything for South Americans.
"It is incomprehensible that the Inter-American Commission on Human Rights is based in Washington and funded by the United States", he said, referring to the political asylum granted by Ecuador to WikiLeaks founder Julian Assange.
Correa assured that he did not regret this decision because it did not betray his principles but was in compliance with his "deep democratic values and views on human rights".
He added that at the time there were "founded suspicions that Assange was extradited to a third country and that his proceedings would not be followed".
He also criticized the Swedish judiciary for requiring him to be interrogated on his territory for an alleged sexual offence, while "Swedish jurisprudence allows this through a video conference that could have been conducted via the Ecuadorian embassy in London".
Correa explained that there was a risk that Assange's health and mental state would be impaired.
